# Coding Agent Style Guide

This document defines coding standards and conventions for this repository to ensure consistency across all contributions.

## General Principles

- **Minimal & Clean**: Keep code simple and purposeful
- **Consistent**: Follow existing patterns
- **Self-Documenting**: Clear naming over excessive comments
- **Mobile-First**: Design for mobile, enhance for desktop

## HTML Conventions

### Structure
```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Page Title - Bahushruth CS</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">
    <link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="potato.svg">
</head>
<body>
    <!-- Navigation is consistent across all pages -->
    <nav class="nav">
        <div class="nav-container">
            <a href="index.html" class="logo" title="Home">
                <img src="potato.svg" alt="Potato" class="potato-icon">
            </a>
            <div class="nav-links">
                <a href="articles.html" class="nav-link">Articles</a>
                <a href="reading.html" class="nav-link">Reading</a>
                <a href="about.html" class="nav-link">About</a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </nav>

    <main class="main">
        <!-- Page content -->
    </main>

    <!-- Footer is consistent across all pages -->
    <footer class="footer">
        <div class="footer-content">
            <p class="footer-text">© 2026 Bahushruth CS</p>
            <div class="footer-social">
                <a href="https://x.com/Bahushruth" target="_blank" class="footer-link">X/Twitter</a>
                <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/bahushruth/" target="_blank" class="footer-link">LinkedIn</a>
                <a href="https://github.com/bahushruth" target="_blank" class="footer-link">GitHub</a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </footer>
</body>
</html>
```

### Rules
- Always include `lang="en"` on `<html>`
- Use relative paths for internal links
- Use `target="_blank"` for external links
- Include the potato favicon on every page
- Navigation must be identical on all pages
- Footer must be identical on all pages

## CSS Conventions

### Naming
- Use **kebab-case** for class names: `.nav-container`, `.hero-title`
- Use semantic class names that describe function, not appearance
- Avoid IDs for styling

### Organization
```css
/* 1. CSS Variables */
:root {
    --bg-primary: #000000;
    /* etc */
}

/* 2. Reset & Base */
* { }
html { }
body { }

/* 3. Layout Components */
.nav { }
.nav-container { }
.main { }
.footer { }

/* 4. Page-Specific Components */
.hero { }
.article-list { }
.reading-section { }

/* 5. Utilities */
.view-all { }
.back-link { }

/* 6. Responsive (always at end) */
@media (max-width: 768px) { }
```

### Colors
Always use CSS variables:
```css
background-color: var(--bg-primary);
color: var(--text-secondary);
border: 1px solid var(--border);
```

### Spacing
- Use `rem` units for all spacing (padding, margins, gaps)
- Base unit: `1rem = 16px`
- Section padding: `4rem 2rem` (desktop), `2rem 1rem` (mobile)
- Component gaps: `1rem`, `1.5rem`, `2rem`

### Borders
- Border radius: `8px` for cards, `0` for profile images (square), `4px` for tags
- Border color: `var(--border)` (#222222)

## Content Guidelines

### Articles
- Use `<article>` tags for article content
- Include `.article-header`, `.article-content`, `.article-tags`
- Use `<h1>` for article title, `<h2>` for sections, `<h3>` for subsections
- Include publication date in meta
- Tags should be lowercase unless proper nouns

### Reading List
- Papers should link directly to arXiv
- Include author names and year
- Add one-line "why" explanation for each paper
- Group papers by topic (Transformers, GNNs, etc.)

### Images
- Profile images: Square corners (`border-radius: 0`)
- Other images: Max 100% width, maintain aspect ratio
- Always include `alt` text

## Git Conventions

### Commit Messages
```
Add: [feature description]
Update: [what changed]
Fix: [what was fixed]
Remove: [what was removed]
```

Examples:
- `Add: new article on Qwen Image Edit`
- `Update: reading list with FlashAttention papers`
- `Fix: mobile navigation layout`

### File Structure
```
/
├── index.html          # Homepage
├── about.html          # About page
├── articles.html       # Articles listing
├── reading.html        # Reading list
├── styles.css          # All styles
├── potato.svg          # Favicon/logo
├── articles/           # Individual article pages
│   └── [article-slug].html
└── pdfs/              # PDF downloads
    └── [paper].pdf
```

## Mobile Responsiveness

### Breakpoints
- Mobile: `< 768px`
- Desktop: `≥ 768px`

### Mobile Rules
- Navigation: Horizontal row, not stacked
- Footer: Stack vertically
- Typography: Slightly smaller (reduce by ~15%)
- Profile image: `100px` instead of `120px`
- Tables: Allow horizontal scroll or stack

## External Links

All external links must:
- Open in new tab (`target="_blank"`)
- Include social links in footer
- Articles/papers link to source

## Accessibility

- Semantic HTML5 tags (`<nav>`, `<main>`, `<article>`, `<footer>`)
- `alt` text on all images
- Sufficient color contrast (WCAG AA)
- Focus states for interactive elements
- Keyboard navigable

## Prohibited

- ❌ Inline styles
- ❌ `!important` (unless absolutely necessary)
- ❌ Frameworks (Bootstrap, Tailwind, etc.) - pure CSS only
- ❌ JavaScript (unless specifically requested)
- ❌ Comments in CSS (unless complex logic)
- ❌ Multiple font families (stick to system fonts)

## Testing Checklist

Before pushing changes:
- [ ] Works on mobile (768px and below)
- [ ] Works on desktop (1200px and above)
- [ ] All links work
- [ ] Images load correctly
- [ ] No console errors
- [ ] Consistent with other pages
- [ ] Valid HTML (check with validator)

## Questions?

When in doubt:
1. Look at existing code
2. Follow the pattern
3. Keep it simple
4. Ask if unsure
